# Key Ideas from Week 2

* Classes
  * Attributes and accessors
  * Recognizing instance variables vs. local variables vs.
    instance methods.
  * Method arguments (splats, defaults, and option hashes)
  * Subclasses and inheritance
  * Modules and mixins
* Jekyll
  * Using provided utilities like `jekyll serve`
  * Markdown and HTML
  * Project layout
  * Git and push-to-deploy workflow

* Errors and exceptions
* Blocks and enumeration (map, reduce, select, reject, etc.)

# Goals for Week 3

* HTML and CSS
* Sinatra
  * Servers and the request -> response cycle
